        "assessmentType": "BuiltIn",
        "policyDefinitionId": "",
        "description": "You can do real-time monitoring of API calls by directing CloudTrail logs to CloudWatch Logs and establishing corresponding metric filters and alarms. Security Hub recommends that you create a metric filter and alarm unauthorized API calls. Monitoring unauthorized API calls helps reveal application errors and might reduce time to detect malicious activity. To run this check, Security Hub uses custom logic to perform the exact audit steps prescribed for control 3.1 in the CIS AWS Foundations Benchmark v1.2. This control fails if the exact metric filters prescribed by CIS are not used. Additional fields or terms cannot be added to the metric filters.",
