        "assessmentType": "BuiltIn",
        "policyDefinitionId": "",
        "description": "This control checks that the default security group of a VPC does not allow inbound or outbound traffic. The rules for the default security group allow all outbound and inbound traffic from network interfaces (and their associated instances) that are assigned to the same security group. We do not recommend using the default security group. Because the default security group cannot be deleted, you should change the default security group rules setting to restrict inbound and outbound traffic. This prevents unintended traffic if the default security group is accidentally configured for resources such as EC2 instances.",
