        "policyDefinitionId": "",
        "description": "This control checks whether Amazon Elastic File System is configured to encrypt the file data using AWS KMS. The check fails in the following cases: 'Encrypted' is set to 'false' in the 'DescribeFileSystems' response; The 'KmsKeyId' key in the 'DescribeFileSystems' response does not match the 'KmsKeyId' parameter for 'efs-encrypted-check'. Note that this control does not use the 'KmsKeyId' parameter for 'efs-encrypted-check'. It only checks the value of 'Encrypted'. For an added layer of security for your sensitive data in Amazon EFS, you should create encrypted file systems. Amazon EFS supports encryption for file systems at-rest. You can enable encryption of data at rest when you create an Amazon EFS file system.",
