        "policyDefinitionId": "",
        "description": "This control checks whether your IAM users have passwords or active access keys that have not been used for 90 days. IAM users can access AWS resources using different types of credentials, such as passwords or access keys. Security Hub recommends that you remove or deactivate all credentials that were unused for 90 days or more. Disabling or removing unnecessary credentials reduces the window of opportunity for credentials associated with a compromised or abandoned account to be used.",
